 <name>lchash</name>
 <channel>pecl.php.net</channel>
 <summary>Linear-probing hash table interface</summary>
 <description>
Wraps glibc hsearch_r where available, otherwise falls back to a small
in-tree open-addressing implementation. Provides four procedural functions
for a single per-request string-keyed hash table:
lchash_create(), lchash_destroy(), lchash_insert(), lchash_find().
 </description>
 <lead>
  <name>Ilia Alshanetsky</name>
  <user>iliaa</user>
  <email>ilia@ilia.ws</email>
  <active>yes</active>
 </lead>
 <date>1970-01-01</date>
 <time>00:00:00</time>
 <version>
  <release>1.0.0</release>
  <api>1.0.0</api>
 </version>
 <stability>
  <release>stable</release>
  <api>stable</api>
 </stability>
 <license uri="https://www.php.net/license/3_01.txt">PHP-3.01</license>
 <notes>
Modernization release. Targets PHP 7.4 through 8.5, NTS and ZTS.
Adds an in-tree fallback so the extension builds on musl, macOS, *BSD,
and Windows in addition to glibc Linux.
 </notes>
